reference "fig:Location-of-Midpoints"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, an appropriately bracketed root will eventually appear, at some finite
 integer 
\begin_inset Formula $p.$
\end_inset

 In general, but not always, 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 will be small.
 The root will always lie in between the two endpoints of the bracketed
