\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice also that the above treatment seems to be a special case of a more
 general principle: when an operator has a continuous spectrum, it can sometimes
 be interpreted as a right-shift.
 That is, given some arbitrary operator 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}$
\end_inset

, then if one has that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}f=\lambda f$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

