 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{m}\left(z\right)$
\end_inset

 be the polynomials, and for some sequence of coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ a_{n}\right\} $
\end_inset

, consider a generic function 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\left(z\right)=\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}a_{k}p_{k}\left(z\right)
\]

\end_inset

Consider the case where the 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ a_{n}\right\} $
\end_inset

 are a right-eigenvector of the Hessenberg operator, that is, where 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}A_{km}a_{m}=\lambda a_{k}
\]

\end_inset

Substituting into the above, one has 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\left(z\right)=\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{\lambda}\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}A_{km}a_{m}p_{k}\left(z\right)=\frac{z}{\lambda}\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}a_{m}p_{m}\left(z\right)=\frac{zf\left(z\right)}{\lambda}
\]

\end_inset

