\begin_inset Formula $\left[\mathcal{D}\right]_{nk}=p_{nn}\delta_{nk}$
\end_inset

.
 With this factorization, one may then write
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{N}^{-1}A^{T}\mathcal{N}=\mathcal{DKD}^{-1}
\]

\end_inset

so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{DKD}^{-1}$
\end_inset

 has off-diagonal matrix entries 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\mathcal{DKD}^{-1}\right]_{nk}=\delta_{n+1,k}p_{nn}/p_{kk}$
\end_inset

